content: Fun to play but frustrating when modern, in-use words are rejected but ancient or misspelt words are accepted. Eg: Palp (arachnid feeler) is "out" but lier (one who lies - eg down) and twerp (sic) are "in". If marketing to a global audience, a more realistic database is required ... otherwise one is tempted to ask "why bother playing?" Well programmed but needs attention to the word sources and usage.
replyContent:
Hi Cass,
Glad to hear you enjoy the game :) You might enjoy playing with 'Expert Words' enabled on Classic- it should accept a lot more of these words. We really appreciate the feedback and will keep this in mind for future updates. And you can always submit words using the 'Suggest a Word' button on the start page!
